reviews.review: The whole movie was "Meh, not bad and definitely not great." It was kind of a messy mish mosh and rehash of bits and pieces and action sequences from the past. The series has lost it's mojo to me. I can see why hard core fans find enough to like and casual fans (like me) can find plenty not to like. I was sort of looking at my watch about 2/3rds through and I knew how everything was going to end. The Star Wars franchise has become more like Marvel movies and honestly the writing has seriously deteriorated. These is nothing new or interesting that makes sense and the Force is anything you want it to be for any episode. It's no longer about enlightenment but simply superpowers. If they do any future movies it will likely be rentals for me. Too bad.

This movie was great. The visuals were absolutely stunning, and the story of the movie didn’t feel forced or boring. The only thing that would have possibilities made this movie better was if George Lucas himself was directing the movie. Daisy Ridley did an amazing job in this movie and I can’t wait to see more of her in the future.
Some cool ideas that were executed poorly. Bad flow and structure. Wasted characters. Old characters didn't feel the same.
I liked the way they explained the generations. And the glimpse of the Ewoks! My favorite!

It's better than The Last Jedi (which doesn't mean a lot), but it's still a bad movie. Rushed, confusing, disappointing... Overall, TROS is a bad movie, and it's insulting to the established lore from Star Wars.

An absolute mess from top to bottom. Enjoy the non stop barrage of fan service designed to distract you from the horrendous script. It had some decent moments, but overall I think it's one of the worst films in the entire franchise. Whether you liked or hated this Last Jedi, that film at least took its time to say something. This was like a fever dream.

The movie was very flawed. 
A lot of retconning took place from the previous movie, and the whole narrative was very rushed. 
It had a few good things about it, but the bad outweigh the good.

It was a fun movie but the plot was a little derivative from Return of the Jedi.  Overall it was Star Wars and thats all that
Matters.
